The paper discusses the use of autoencoders and generative adversarial networks for anomaly detection in sequence data. This falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of generative adversarial networks also suggests a potential application in computer vision (cs.CV) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the use of oversampling techniques and outlier detection methods suggests a potential application in neural networks (cs.NE).
